-- Brazil Central Bank's Pereira Warns of `Excessive Irrational Exuberance'
-- Michael Patterson
-- 2010-06-24T09:13:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/brazil-central-bank-s-pereira-warns-of-excessive-irrational-exuberance-.html

          
          
             Brazil needs to avoid “excessive
irrational exuberance,” said Luiz Pereira, director of
international affairs at Brazil’s central bank.  
 Pereira spoke today at “The Sovereign Debt Briefing” in
London hosted by Bloomberg Link.  
          
          


  


        